cpqSMAAgentRefreshTime.name: cpqSMAAgentRefreshTime
cpqSMAAgentRefreshTime.description: The time interval before the next data collection. The information about the HSG80 is collected periodically. A thread gathers the information and stores it in memory. This variable is used to specify the time interval in minutes (MINUTES) between each update.

cpqSMAAgentHostName.name: cpqSMAAgentHostName
cpqSMAAgentHostName.description: The name of the local machine where the agent is running.

cpqSMASubsystemEntry.name: cpqSMASubsystemEntry
cpqSMASubsystemEntry.description: A table entry for a Subsystem

cpqSMASubsystemControllerOne.name: cpqSMASubsystemControllerOne
cpqSMASubsystemControllerOne.description: The index of controller one thats belongs to this subsytem. If the value is -1 then either the controller is not installed or not operational.

cpqSMASubsystemControllerTwo.name: cpqSMASubsystemControllerTwo
cpqSMASubsystemControllerTwo.description: The index of controller two thats belongs to this subsytem. If the value is -1 then either the controller is not installed or not operational.

cpqSMASubsystemEMUState.name: cpqSMASubsystemEMUState
cpqSMASubsystemEMUState.description: Subsystem Environmental Monitoring Unit (EMU) State. nooper(1) - EMU is either not installed or not operational. oper(2) - EMU is operational.

cpqSMASubsystemEMUVersion.name: cpqSMASubsystemEMUVersion
cpqSMASubsystemEMUVersion.description: Subsystem Environmental Monitoring Unit (EMU) Microcode verion.

cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor1.name: cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor1
cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor1.description: Subsystem Environmental Monitoring Unit (EMU) Sensor1 value (in Celsius). Sensor1 sets the maximum operating temperature for the primary subsystem cabinet.

cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor2.name: cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor2
cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor2.description: Subsystem Environmental Monitoring Unit (EMU) Sensor2 value (in Celsius). Sensor2 also sets the maximum operating temperature for the primary subsystem cabinet.

cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor3.name: cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor3
cpqSMASubsystemEMUSensor3.description: Subsystem Environmental Monitoring Unit (EMU) Sensor3 value (in Celsius). Sensor3 sets the maximum operating temperature for the EMU unit.

cpqSMASubsystemEMUFanspeed.name: cpqSMASubsystemEMUFanspeed
cpqSMASubsystemEMUFanspeed.description: Subsystem Fanspeed. FANSPEED=HIGH forces the fans in all connected cabinets to operate at high speed continuously. FANSPEED=AUTOMATIC allows the EMU to control the fan speed for the fans in all connected cabinets. The EMU instructs the fans to operate at high speed when any of the temperature setpoints are exceeded or when one or more fans are not functioning.

cpqSMASubsystemEMUAlarm.name: cpqSMASubsystemEMUAlarm
cpqSMASubsystemEMUAlarm.description: Subsystem Environmental Monitoring Unit Alarm. Determines whether or not the audible alarm of the EMU will sound in the following cases: drive failure controller restart The EMU alarm will still sound in the event of an adverse environmental condition, such as a power failure or an over-temperature condition.

cpqSMASubsystemState.name: cpqSMASubsystemState
cpqSMASubsystemState.description: Gives us the overall state of the HSG80 subsystem.

cpqSMAControllerEntry.name: cpqSMAControllerEntry
cpqSMAControllerEntry.description: A table entry for a controller

cpqSMAControllerSerialNumber.name: cpqSMAControllerSerialNumber
cpqSMAControllerSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the controller.

cpqSMAControllerHardware.name: cpqSMAControllerHardware
cpqSMAControllerHardware.description: The hardware revision of the controller.

cpqSMAControllerNodeID.name: cpqSMAControllerNodeID
cpqSMAControllerNodeID.description: Manufacturer assigned ID of the controller.

cpqSMAControllerIdentifier.name: cpqSMAControllerIdentifier
cpqSMAControllerIdentifier.description: The user assigned identifier if any of the controller.

cpqSMAControllerScsiVersion.name: cpqSMAControllerScsiVersion
cpqSMAControllerScsiVersion.description: The scsi version of the controller

cpqSMAControllerRedundancy.name: cpqSMAControllerRedundancy
cpqSMAControllerRedundancy.description: The redundancy type of the controller

cpqSMAControllerScsiID.name: cpqSMAControllerScsiID
cpqSMAControllerScsiID.description: The device port scsi address of the controller

cpqSMAControllerCacheSize.name: cpqSMAControllerCacheSize
cpqSMAControllerCacheSize.description: The cache size in megabytes. Can be either 64, 128, 256 or 512 MB.

cpqSMAControllerCacheType.name: cpqSMAControllerCacheType
cpqSMAControllerCacheType.description: The cache type of this controller

cpqSMAControllerCacheVersion.name: cpqSMAControllerCacheVersion
cpqSMAControllerCacheVersion.description: The version of this controllers cache.

cpqSMAControllerCacheFlushTimer.name: cpqSMAControllerCacheFlushTimer
cpqSMAControllerCacheFlushTimer.description: The cache flush timer in sec

cpqSMAControllerMirrorCache.name: cpqSMAControllerMirrorCache
cpqSMAControllerMirrorCache.description: The mirror cache state of this controller

cpqSMAControllerPairIndex.name: cpqSMAControllerPairIndex
cpqSMAControllerPairIndex.description: The index of this controller's pair if FAILOVER mode (cpqSMAControllerRedundancy) is mutlibus or transparent. If there is no FAILOVER mode (cpqSMAControllerRedundancy is single or unknown) then the value is -1.

cpqSMAControllerCacheState.name: cpqSMAControllerCacheState
cpqSMAControllerCacheState.description: The state of the controller cache.

cpqSMAControllerBatteryCheckState.name: cpqSMAControllerBatteryCheckState
cpqSMAControllerBatteryCheckState.description: Battery check state. Specifies whether the controller should perform regular battery condition checks. If CACHE-UPS (ups) the controller does not check the condition of the cache batteries and ignores the battery's state. If NOCACHE-UPS (noups) the controller performs regular cache battery checks and evaluates the condition of the cache batteries.

cpqSMAControllerBatteryChargeState.name: cpqSMAControllerBatteryChargeState
cpqSMAControllerBatteryChargeState.description: This is the value in % (percentage) of the amount the controller battery is charged. A value of 0 (zero) means DANGER: BATTERY LIFETIME HAS EXPIRED, REPLACE BATTERY NOW!.

cpqSMAControllerBatteryExpiryDate.name: cpqSMAControllerBatteryExpiryDate
cpqSMAControllerBatteryExpiryDate.description: The expiry date of the controller battery.

cpqSMAControllerSubsystemIndex.name: cpqSMAControllerSubsystemIndex
cpqSMAControllerSubsystemIndex.description: The index of the subsystem to which this controller belongs.

cpqSMAControllerLogicalDiskIndexes.name: cpqSMAControllerLogicalDiskIndexes
cpqSMAControllerLogicalDiskIndexes.description: The indexes of all the logical disks associated with the controller. Each index is seperated by a ':' .

cpqSMAControllerSnapshotIndexes.name: cpqSMAControllerSnapshotIndexes
cpqSMAControllerSnapshotIndexes.description: The indexes of all the snapshots associated with the controller. Each index is seperated by a ':' .

cpqSMALogicalDiskEntry.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskEntry
cpqSMALogicalDiskEntry.description: A table entry for a LogicalDisk

cpqSMALogicalDiskIndex.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskIndex
cpqSMALogicalDiskIndex.description: The LogicalDisk index. This is just a ordered sequence done by the agent, has no relationship to the unit offset or unit name/number.

cpqSMALogicalDiskSize.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskSize
cpqSMALogicalDiskSize.description: Logical Drive Size. This is the size of the logical drive in blocks. One block equals 512 bytes (1 block = 512 bytes).

cpqSMALogicalDiskCreatedFromIndex.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskCreatedFromIndex
cpqSMALogicalDiskCreatedFromIndex.description: Logical Drive Created From Instance. This gives us the instance of the storageset or physical disk from which this LUN was created.

cpqSMALogicalDiskReadCache.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskReadCache
cpqSMALogicalDiskReadCache.description: Logical Drive Read Cache. The state of the read cache for the associated logical drives.

cpqSMALogicalDiskWriteBackCache.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskWriteBackCache
cpqSMALogicalDiskWriteBackCache.description: Logical Drive WriteBack Cache. The state of the writeback cache for the associated logical drives.

cpqSMALogicalDiskWriteProtectCache.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskWriteProtectCache
cpqSMALogicalDiskWriteProtectCache.description: Logical Drive WriteProtect Cache. The state of the write protect cache for the associated logical drives.

cpqSMALogicalDiskReadAheadCache.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskReadAheadCache
cpqSMALogicalDiskReadAheadCache.description: Logical Drive ReadAhead Cache. The state of the readahead cache for the associated logical drives.

cpqSMALogicalDiskRunState.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskRunState
cpqSMALogicalDiskRunState.description: Logical Drive Run State. The run state for the associated logical drives. you specify RUN to make a unit available to the host.

cpqSMALogicalDiskState.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskState
cpqSMALogicalDiskState.description: Logical Drive State. The state of the associated logical drive.

cpqSMALogicalDiskCachedTransferSize.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskCachedTransferSize
cpqSMALogicalDiskCachedTransferSize.description: Logical Drive CachedTransferSize. The largest number of write blocks to be cached by the controller. The controller will not cache any transfers over the specified size.

cpqSMALogicalDiskPreferredPath.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskPreferredPath
cpqSMALogicalDiskPreferredPath.description: Logical Drive PreferredPath. May be set only when dual redundant controllers are operating in a multiple-bus failover configuration.

cpqSMALogicalDiskHostAccess.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskHostAccess
cpqSMALogicalDiskHostAccess.description: Logical Drive Host Access. Specifies the access path.

cpqSMALogicalDiskIdentifier.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskIdentifier
cpqSMALogicalDiskIdentifier.description: Logical Drive ID (Lun-ID) This ID consists of the controller node ID plus a 64-bit unit ID generated by the subsystem.

cpqSMALogicalDiskControllerInstance.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskControllerInstance
cpqSMALogicalDiskControllerInstance.description: Logical Drive Controller Instance. This gives us the instance of the controller to which this LUN is online.

cpqSMALogicalDiskCreatedFromType.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskCreatedFromType
cpqSMALogicalDiskCreatedFromType.description: Logical Drive Created from type. Tells us whether the LUN was created from an entire physical disk, entire storageset or from a partition(logical or physical). cpqSMALogicalDiskCreatedFromIndex gives us the instance of the object.

cpqSMALogicalDiskIdentifierSwitch.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskIdentifierSwitch
cpqSMALogicalDiskIdentifierSwitch.description: Logical Drive Identifier switch. This is used with the SCSI-VERSION switch when the SCSI version is set to SCSI-3 mode. The IDENTIFIER switch creates a unique unit identifier makes the unit visible to the host.This number can be a value between 1-9999. The value 0 means NOIDENTIFIER.

cpqSMALogicalDiskSnapped.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskSnapped
cpqSMALogicalDiskSnapped.description: Logical Drive Snapped. This tells us if a snapshot of this disk exists.

cpqSMALogicalDiskSnapshotInstance.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskSnapshotInstance
cpqSMALogicalDiskSnapshotInstance.description: Logical Drive Snapshot instance. If the disk has a snapshot ie. cpqSMALogicalDiskSnapped is yes, then this gives us the instance of the snapshot else -1.

cpqSMALogicalDiskSubsystemIndex.name: cpqSMALogicalDiskSubsystemIndex
cpqSMALogicalDiskSubsystemIndex.description: The index of the subsystem where this logical disk resides.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskEntry.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskEntry
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskEntry.description: A table entry for a PhysicalDisk

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskSize.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskSize
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskSize.description: Physical Disk Size. This is the size of the physical disk in megabytes. This value is calculated using the value 1,048,576 (2^20) as a megabyte. Drive manufacturers sometimes use the number 1,000,000 as a megabyte when giving drive capacities so this value may differ from the advertised size of a drive.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskTransportable.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskTransportable
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskTransportable.description: PhysicalDisk Transportable. Indicates whether a disk drive can be accessed exclusively by StorageWorks.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskTransferRate.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskTransferRate
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskTransferRate.description: PhysicalDisk Transportable. Indicates whether a disk drive can be accessed exclusively by StorageWorks.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskState.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskState
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskState.description: PhysicalDisk State. Indicates whether a disk drive has been assigend to a storageset, lun or not.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskUsedByIndex.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskUsedByIndex
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskUsedByIndex.description: PhysicalDisk Used by index. This is the index of the lun or storageset that was created by using this physical disk. If the disk is unassigned or free ie. cpqSMAPhysicalDiskState = 1 then the index is of the this controller.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskNoofPartitions.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskNoofPartitions
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskNoofPartitions.description: The number of partitions on this PhysicalDisk.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskUsedByType.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskUsedByType
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskUsedByType.description: PhysicalDisk UsedByType. If this disk has been assigned ie. cpqSMAPhysicalDiskState = 2, then this indicates the type of object that was created using this disk ie. whether it is a storageset or a lun and cpqSMAPhysicalDiskUsedByIndex gives you the instance of that object.

cpqSMAPhysicalDiskSubsystemIndex.name: cpqSMAPhysicalDiskSubsystemIndex
cpqSMAPhysicalDiskSubsystemIndex.description: The index of the subsystem where this physical disk resides.

cpqSMAStorageSetEntry.name: cpqSMAStorageSetEntry
cpqSMAStorageSetEntry.description: A table entry for a StorageSet

cpqSMAStorageSetSize.name: cpqSMAStorageSetSize
cpqSMAStorageSetSize.description: Storageset Size. This is the size of the storagset disk in megabytes. This value is calculated using the value 1,048,576 (2^20) as a megabyte. Drive manufacturers sometimes use the number 1,000,000 as a megabyte when giving drive capacities so this value may differ from the advertised size of a drive.

cpqSMAStorageSetPolicy.name: cpqSMAStorageSetPolicy
cpqSMAStorageSetPolicy.description: The StorageSet Policy switch. Sets the selection criteria the contoller uses to choose a replacement disk from the spareset. This policy only pertains to MIRRORSETs and RAIDSETs. For the other types it will be set to unknown.

cpqSMAStorageSetReconstruct.name: cpqSMAStorageSetReconstruct
cpqSMAStorageSetReconstruct.description: The StorageSet Reconstruct switch. Sets the speed at which the contoller reconstructs data ti a new RAIDset disk that replaces the failed disk. This policy only pertains to RAIDSETs. For the other types it will be set to unknown.

cpqSMAStorageSetCopy.name: cpqSMAStorageSetCopy
cpqSMAStorageSetCopy.description: The StorageSet Copy switch. Sets the speed at which the controller copies data to a new member from normal mirrorset members when data is being mirrored to the storageset's disk drives. This policy only pertains to MIRRORSETs. For the other types it will be set to unknown.

cpqSMAStorageSetReadSource.name: cpqSMAStorageSetReadSource
cpqSMAStorageSetReadSource.description: The Storageset ReadSource switch. Selects the mirrorset member used by the controller to satisfy a read request. The values will be either - disk-name (name of the specific member to which you want the controller to direct all read requests) - least-busy - round-robin This policy only pertains to MIRRORSETs. For the other types it will be set to unknown.

cpqSMAStorageSetAutospare.name: cpqSMAStorageSetAutospare
cpqSMAStorageSetAutospare.description: The StorageSet Autospare switch. With autospare enabled on a failedset, any new disk drive that is inserted into the PTL location of a failed dusk drive is automatically initialized and placed into the spareset. This policy only pertains to FAILEDSET. For the other types it will be set to unknown.

cpqSMAStorageSetChunkSize.name: cpqSMAStorageSetChunkSize
cpqSMAStorageSetChunkSize.description: The StorageSet ChunkSize switch. Specify a chunk size to control the stripesize used for RAIDsets and stripesets in blocks. This policy only pertains to RAIDSETs and STRIPESETs. For the other types it will be set to zero.

cpqSMAStorageSetNoOfDisks.name: cpqSMAStorageSetNoOfDisks
cpqSMAStorageSetNoOfDisks.description: The number of the physical disks that was used to create this StorageSet.

cpqSMAStorageSetDisksIndex.name: cpqSMAStorageSetDisksIndex
cpqSMAStorageSetDisksIndex.description: The indexes of the physical disks from which this StorageSet was created. Each index is seperated by a ':' .

cpqSMAStorageSetState.name: cpqSMAStorageSetState
cpqSMAStorageSetState.description: Storageset State. Indicates whether a lun has been created from the storageset.

cpqSMAStorageSetUsedByIndex.name: cpqSMAStorageSetUsedByIndex
cpqSMAStorageSetUsedByIndex.description: Storageset Used by index. This is the index of the lun or snapshot that was created from this storageset. If the storageset is unassigned or free ie. cpqSMAStorageSetState = 1 then the index is of the this controller. If the storageset has multiple (>1) partitions then the value is -1.

cpqSMAStorageSetNoofPartitions.name: cpqSMAStorageSetNoofPartitions
cpqSMAStorageSetNoofPartitions.description: The number of partitions on this Storageset.

cpqSMAStorageSetSubsystemIndex.name: cpqSMAStorageSetSubsystemIndex
cpqSMAStorageSetSubsystemIndex.description: The index of the subsystem where this storageset resides.

cpqSMAStorageSetUsedByType.name: cpqSMAStorageSetUsedByType
cpqSMAStorageSetUsedByType.description: Storageset Used by index. This tells us whether the type of disk created from this storageset is a lun or a snapshot. ie. if cpqSMAStorageSetState = 2 (assigned) then this tells you the type (lun or snapshot) and cpqSMAStorageSetUsedByIndex gives the index of that object.

cpqSMAPartitionEntry.name: cpqSMAPartitionEntry
cpqSMAPartitionEntry.description: A table entry for a Partition

cpqSMAPartitionDeviceIndex.name: cpqSMAPartitionDeviceIndex
cpqSMAPartitionDeviceIndex.description: The Partition Device Index. This is the index of the device (physical) or storageset (logical) from which this partition was created.

cpqSMAPartitionUsedByIndex.name: cpqSMAPartitionUsedByIndex
cpqSMAPartitionUsedByIndex.description: The Partition Used By Index. This is the index of the lun that was created from this partition. If the parition is unassigned or free ie. cpqSMAPartitionDeviceState = 1 then the index is of the this controller.

cpqSMAPartitionSize.name: cpqSMAPartitionSize
cpqSMAPartitionSize.description: Partition Size. This is the size of the partition in megabytes. This value is calculated using the value 1,048,576 (2^20) as a megabyte. Drive manufacturers sometimes use the number 1,000,000 as a megabyte when giving drive capacities so this value may differ from the advertised size of a drive.

cpqSMAPartitionType.name: cpqSMAPartitionType
cpqSMAPartitionType.description: The type of Partition. If its a partition created from a device(disk) its a physical partition if its created from a storageset then its a logical partition.

cpqSMAPartitionSubsystemIndex.name: cpqSMAPartitionSubsystemIndex
cpqSMAPartitionSubsystemIndex.description: The index of the subsystem where this partition resides.

cpqSMAConnectionEntry.name: cpqSMAConnectionEntry
cpqSMAConnectionEntry.description: A table entry for a Connection

cpqSMAConnectionController.name: cpqSMAConnectionController
cpqSMAConnectionController.description: The instance of the controller to which there is a connection.

cpqSMAConnectionControllerPortNumber.name: cpqSMAConnectionControllerPortNumber
cpqSMAConnectionControllerPortNumber.description: The port number on the controller to which there is a connection.

cpqSMAConnectionOnlineTo.name: cpqSMAConnectionOnlineTo
cpqSMAConnectionOnlineTo.description: The instance of the controller to which it is online.

cpqSMAConnectionLunOffset.name: cpqSMAConnectionLunOffset
cpqSMAConnectionLunOffset.description: The LUN offset for this connection.

cpqSMAConnectionSubsystemIndex.name: cpqSMAConnectionSubsystemIndex
cpqSMAConnectionSubsystemIndex.description: The index of the subsystem where this connection exists.

cpqSMASnapshotEntry.name: cpqSMASnapshotEntry
cpqSMASnapshotEntry.description: A table entry for a Snapshot

cpqSMASnapshotSize.name: cpqSMASnapshotSize
cpqSMASnapshotSize.description: Snapshot Drive Size. This is the size of the snapshot in blocks. One block equals 512 bytes (1 block = 512 bytes).

cpqSMASnapshotCreatedFromIndex.name: cpqSMASnapshotCreatedFromIndex
cpqSMASnapshotCreatedFromIndex.description: Snapshot Created From Instance. This gives us the instance of the storageset from which this snapshot was created.

cpqSMASnapshotOf.name: cpqSMASnapshotOf
cpqSMASnapshotOf.description: This is the instance of the logical disk for which this is a snapshot.

cpqSMASnapshotState.name: cpqSMASnapshotState
cpqSMASnapshotState.description: Snapshot State. The state of the snapshot.

cpqSMASnapshotPreferredPath.name: cpqSMASnapshotPreferredPath
cpqSMASnapshotPreferredPath.description: Snapshot PreferredPath. May be set only when dual redundant controllers are operating in a multiple-bus failover configuration.

cpqSMASnapshotHostAccess.name: cpqSMASnapshotHostAccess
cpqSMASnapshotHostAccess.description: Snapshot Host Access. Specifies the access path.

cpqSMASnapshotIdentifier.name: cpqSMASnapshotIdentifier
cpqSMASnapshotIdentifier.description: Snapshot ID This ID consists of the controller node ID plus a 64-bit unit ID generated by the subsystem.

cpqSMASnapshotControllerInstance.name: cpqSMASnapshotControllerInstance
cpqSMASnapshotControllerInstance.description: Snapshot Controller Instance. This gives us the instance of the controller to which this snapshot is online.

cpqSMASnapshotIdentifierSwitch.name: cpqSMASnapshotIdentifierSwitch
cpqSMASnapshotIdentifierSwitch.description: Snapshot Identifier switch. This is used with the SCSI-VERSION switch when the SCSI version is set to SCSI-3 mode. The IDENTIFIER switch creates a unique unit identifier makes the unit visible to the host.This number can be a value between 1-9999. The value 0 means NOIDENTIFIER.

cpqSMASnapshotSubsystemIndex.name: cpqSMASnapshotSubsystemIndex
cpqSMASnapshotSubsystemIndex.description: The index of the subsystem where this snapshot resides.
